<title>UK: RESEARCH ALERT-STV started as &quot;underperform&quot;.</title>
<headline>RESEARCH ALERT-STV started as &quot;underperform&quot;.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-10-24</dateline>
<text>
<p>Scottish Television Plc was rated &quot;underperform&quot; as analysts at Salomon Brothers began coverage of the stock, a research note from analysts Ivor Jones, David Forster and Richard Dale said on Thursday.  </p>
<p>The note said takeover speculation had led to a 14 percent premium in the stock compared with what was justified on the fundamentals and that if a takeover was launched its price might disappoint.</p>
<p>It said obvious bidders were not so obvious on closer inspection, and that it could be correction time for a stock which had risen 70 percent this year.</p>
<p>&quot;Despite a good trading performance, we think the risks outweigh potential rewards,&quot; the note said.</p>
<p>The stock was unchanged at 776-1/2p by 0743 GMT.</p>
<p>-- David Holmes, London Newsroom +44 171 542 5106</p>
